@startuml Payment-Gated Data Exchange
title **Use Case: Payment-Gated Data Exchange (post-prototype)**\nA consumer is gated from data transfer until external payment is confirmed via the connector

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #424242
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #9E9E9E
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam noteBorderColor #F9A825
skinparam sequenceGroupBackgroundColor #FFF3E0
skinparam sequenceGroupBorderColor #EF6C00
skinparam sequenceDividerBackgroundColor #F3E5F5

actor "Consumer\n(corporate analyst)" as Consumer #FFF3E0
participant "Consumer\nEDC Connector" as C_EDC #E3F2FD
participant "Provider\nEDC Connector\n+ payment-status\nextension" as P_EDC #E8F5E9
actor "Provider\nFinance/Ops\n(email recipient)" as Finance #E8F5E9
participant "External Billing /\nPayment system" as Pay #F3E5F5

== Setup ==

note over P_EDC
  Provider publishes asset with the
  **payment-required** contract policy:
  - Permission: **use**, with duty to **pay** by deadline
  - Prohibition: use if payAmount != agreed OR past deadline
  - Obligation: provider compensates if consumer paid
    but access was denied (refund clause)
  - Consequence: invalidate agreement on duty breach
  See PAYMENT_GATING.md §1 for the full template.
end note

== Catalog Discovery & Contract Negotiation (compressed) ==

Consumer -> C_EDC : Browse provider catalog
C_EDC -> P_EDC : DSP Catalog Query
P_EDC --> C_EDC : Catalog with offer (payment-required)
C_EDC --> Consumer : Offer with terms\n(amount, deadline, refund clause)
Consumer -> C_EDC : Accept terms
C_EDC -> P_EDC : DSP Contract Negotiation
P_EDC -> P_EDC : Negotiation reaches **FINALIZED**

== Finalization & Email Notification ==

group NegotiationFinalizedObserver
  P_EDC -> P_EDC : Stamp privateProperties:\npayment.status = "pending"\npayment.amount, payment.currency,\npayment.deadline\n(sourced from the policy template)
  P_EDC -> Finance : **Email** with negotiation ID,\nagreement summary, amount,\ndeadline, payment-update endpoint
end
note right of Finance
  Async send off the state-machine
  thread. SMTP host + recipient
  pulled from extension config
  (PAYMENT_GATING.md §6.1).
end note

== Premature Transfer Attempt - rejected by the gate ==

Consumer -> C_EDC : Request transfer (before payment)
C_EDC -> P_EDC : POST /v3/transferprocesses
group PaymentRequiredFilter
  P_EDC -> P_EDC : Read privateProperties:\npayment.status == "pending"\n=> **REJECT**
end
P_EDC --> C_EDC : **HTTP 402 Payment Required**
C_EDC --> Consumer : Transfer rejected - payment pending

== External Payment ==

Finance -> Pay : Issue invoice for negotiation
Pay --> Consumer : Invoice (out-of-band channel\nowned by the billing system)
Consumer -> Pay : Pay invoice
Pay --> Finance : Payment confirmed\n(externalRef: e.g. stripe_pi_3MXa...)

== Payment Status Update - back-channel into the connector ==

Finance -> P_EDC : POST /v3/contractnegotiations/{id}/payment\nX-Api-Key: ...\n{paid: true, amount: "100.00",\n currency: "USD", externalRef: "..."}
group PaymentController
  P_EDC -> P_EDC : Verify FINALIZED + has Agreement
  P_EDC -> P_EDC : Idempotent on externalRef
  P_EDC -> P_EDC : Write privateProperties:\npayment.status = "paid"\npayment.paidAt = now()\npayment.externalRef
end
P_EDC --> Finance : 200 OK

== Successful Transfer ==

Consumer -> C_EDC : Request transfer
C_EDC -> P_EDC : POST /v3/transferprocesses
group PaymentRequiredFilter (v0)
  P_EDC -> P_EDC : payment.status == "paid" ✓\nnow() <= payment.deadline ✓\n=> **PASS**
end
group ODRL constraint functions (v1, forward-compatible)
  P_EDC -> P_EDC : payAmount == agreed? **YES**\npaymentStatus == completed? **YES**\ndateTime <= deadline? **YES**
end
P_EDC -> P_EDC : DSP Transfer initiated
P_EDC --> C_EDC : Data payload
C_EDC --> Consumer : Transfer complete

== Audit substrate (always available) ==

note over P_EDC
  Dataspace Authority (and either party)
  can call (with X-Api-Key):
  - **GET** /v3/contractnegotiations/{id}/obligations
    → returns clauses extracted from the agreement
       (duty, prohibition, obligation, consequence)
  - **GET** /v3/contractnegotiations/{id}/audit
    → returns payment.* transitions, lifecycle states,
       transfer-process attempts, terminationReason
  Substrate for refund-claim adjudication and
  Trust Framework compliance reviews.
  An aggregating service + UI on the Authority side
  is **proposed** (PAYMENT_GATING.md §3.3) - not built yet.
end note

== If deadline passes without payment (v2) ==

/ note over P_EDC, Consumer
  **DutyDeadlineEnforcer (v2)** runs hourly:
  1. Find negotiations where deadline elapsed and payment.status != paid
  2. Stamp payment.terminationReason = "payment.duty.deadline-exceeded:<duty-uri>"
  3. POST /v3/contractnegotiations/{id}/terminate
     → DSP **ContractNegotiationTermination** propagates to the consumer's connector
     → both sides converge on **TERMINATED**
  4. Cascade-terminate any in-flight transfer-processes
  Once terminated, EDC core refuses any future transfer creation
  upstream of the v0 filter - the deadline check in the filter becomes redundant.
end note

@enduml
